title.narrative: DEVELOPING AND APPLYING SKILLS

description.narrative: Young people are provided with the opportunities to develop and apply their skills to successfully transition to work., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, young people, particularly the most vulnerable and marginalized, have increased knowledge, skills and opportunities to practise healthy lifestyles, participate in decision-making and make the transition to working life

description.narrative: ;In partnership with MOLEVSA, an innovative programme providing vulnerable young people with internship opportunities was launched, following establishment of the multi-stakeholder Advisory Board co-chaired by the National Employment Service (NES); 68 NES case managers from across Serbia were trained on how to better reach out to vulnerable young people. Initial steps on using UNICEF’s global Yoma platform were made. UNICEF supported the Government in the development of a new Law on Internships and has secured its support in the further self-sustainability of the programme. Till end of year 1097 youth were engaged.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/12/2021
